title.english: Life With an Ordinary Guy Who Reincarnated Into a Total Fantasy Knockout

description:
Childhood friends Tachibana Hinata and Jinguuji Tsukasa were living the everyday life of office workers. Then, on the way home from a mixer, they were sent flying into another world by a mysterious being. Once there, Jinguuji sees his best friend has been turned into a beautiful blonde-haired, blue-eyed girl...?!

The adorableness of Tachibana’s female form completely flummoxes Tachibana. But these two are each others’ best friends. To keep their relationship from being destroyed, they must defeat the Demon Lord as quickly as possible and return to their original forms.

(Source: Crunchyroll)

tags.name: Gender Bending
tags.description: Prominently features a character who dresses and behaves in a way characteristic of another gender, or has been transformed into a person of another gender.

tags.name: Isekai
tags.description: Features characters being transported into an alternate world setting and having to adapt to their new surroundings.

tags.name: Slapstick
tags.description: Prominently features comedy based on deliberately clumsy actions or embarrassing events.

tags.name: LGBTQ+ Themes
tags.description: Prominently features characters or themes associated with the LGBTQ+ community, such as sexuality or gender identity.

tags.name: Primarily Adult Cast
tags.description: Main cast is mostly composed of characters above a high school age.

tags.name: Parody
tags.description: Features deliberate exaggeration of popular tropes or a particular genre to comedic effect.

tags.name: Boys' Love
tags.description: Prominently features romance between two males, not inherently sexual.

tags.name: Gods
tags.description: Prominently features a character of divine or religious nature.

tags.name: Magic
tags.description: Prominently features magical elements or the use of magic.

tags.name: Shounen
tags.description: Target demographic is teenage and young adult males.

tags.name: Satire
tags.description: Prominently features the use of comedy or ridicule to expose and criticise social phenomena.

tags.name: Meta
tags.description: Features fourth wall-breaking references to itself or genre tropes.

tags.name: Heterosexual
tags.description: Prominently features a romance between a man and a woman, not inherently sexual.

tags.name: Elf
tags.description: Prominently features a character who is an elf.

tags.name: Chuunibyou
tags.description: Prominently features a character with "Middle School 2nd Year Syndrome", who either acts like a know-it-all adult or falsely believes they have special powers.

tags.name: Travel
tags.description: Centers around character(s) moving between places a significant distance apart.

tags.name: Vore
tags.description: Features a character being swallowed or swallowing another creature whole.

A Japanese musician, singer and songwriter. He originally became known on an international level for his work in the anime [Macross 7](https://anilist.co/anime/1397/) where he was the singing voice and guitar of the show's main character, [Basara Nekki](https://anilist.co/character/4817/). Fukuyama is currently enjoying a successful career recording both solo and member of the anison band JAM Project.

node.description: Alternate names: Tenchuu Girls Date of birth: Dec 30, 2012 Website Associates in Arc Jewel. Appeared as trainees of Lovely★Doll (愛乙女★DOLL) on December 30, 2012. The unit name changed to Love☆Ken (らぶ☆けん) on December 24, 2013. The unit was separated into two: Love☆Ken Luce and Love☆Ken Stella on February 2, 2014, and they were Love☆Ken Luce. The unit name changed to Luce Twinkle Wink☆ on May 23, 2014. The unit was also Tenchuu Girls (天誅ガールズ) from Black Bullet with dancer Kanami Sawaguchi (Tenchuu Green) and Seiyuu Erika Kaiho (Tenchuu Black), and participated Animelo Summer Live 2015 -THE GATE- on August 29, 2015 as backdancers of fripSide. The unit major debut via NBC Universal Entertainment Japan with Koiiro♡Shikoukairo on November 25, 2015. Members: Usami Yukino (Twinkle Pink) - was Tenchuu Pink from Tenchuu Girls Saori Itayama (Twinkle Water Blue) - was Tenchuu Blue from Tenchuu Girls Kaho Higaki (Twinkle Lavender) - originally from C-ZONE, was Rusuban Pink from Rusuban Girls and Tenchuu Violet from Tenchuu Girls Saki Fukasawa (Twinkle Red) - originally from coro☆coro with Saki Fukasawa, was Tenchuu Red from Tenchuu Girls Megumi Nishikiori (Twinkle Yellow) - originally from Hydrangea, was Tenchuu Yellow from Tenchuu Girls (Source: MAL)

[Website](http://apphiayu.com/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/soymilkpudding)

Apphia Yu, also known as Ayu Sakata, is an American voice actress, director, and producer. She has worked on games such as Loren The Amazon Princess and Tales of Aravorn: Seasons of the Wolf, or for anime like Assassination Classroom. She is the founder of sakevisual, a company based in Dallas, Texas that makes original visual novel games. She is married to voice actor [Micah Solusod](https://anilist.co/staff/103686/).

(Source: Wikipedia)
